<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-251-788  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 251 788.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  March 16 1990 n1386* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (England) 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>And Microsoft commits to Truetype for Windows, PresentationManager environments.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microsoft Corp. (product development)Apple Computer Inc. (products).andO;Ticker:    MSFT; AAPL.andO;Product:   OS (Presentation Manager (Graphical user interface)_computerprograms)Microsoft Windows (Graphical user interface) (computer programs).andO;Topic:     Page Description LanguagesFontsNew Technique.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>AND MICROSOFT COMMITS TO TRUETYPE FOR WINDOWS,andM;PRESENTATION MANAGER ENVORONMENTSandM;Microsoft Corp is to provide the TrueType outline font technology adopted byApple Computer Inc in preference to Adobe Systems' offering in MicrosoftWindows and in OS/2 Pre-sentation Manager version 2.0.andP;  The company has alsoannounced that Microsoft TrueImage will be the name for its page descriptionlanguage, announced in September 1989, which incorporates the TrueType fontformat.andP;  TrueType, also known as Royal, is an outline font technology thatdisplays text of any size at high or low resolution, on any screen orprinter.andP;  The open format means all hardware, software and font vendors canadapt their products to support a consistent set of fonts for both the screenand printer.andP;  Both Apple Computer and Microsoft have agreed to providestandard font technology for their operating environments to allow theexchange of text documents between the Macintosh System 7, OS/2 PresentationManager and Windows.andP;  The software that that executes the commands in thefont file to create the fonts used by a printer or graphics display is theTruetype rasteriser.andP;  Software vendors that have announced they will licensethe rasteriser include Aldus Corp, the Microsoft applications group, SoftwarePublishing, and WordPerfect.andP;  TrueImage 1.0, a printer software superset ofthe PostScript page description language, and expected in products sometimethis year, will support the TrueType font format.andP;  The TrueImage languageuses TrueType outline font format and Microsoft says that it providessuperior WYSIWYG for any application running under Microsoft's graphic userinterfaces.andO;</TEXT></DOC>